Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.38,0:48:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Get a move on{tbh no clue what's 行けや in kansai}, #2 rider. {volume 8 page 76}{it's like a "get a moce on" kinda thing in my head} {I had no idea what it meant in JApanese initially, now I can't wrap my head around what it means in English either, amazing. - PErevo}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.84,0:48:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.84,0:48:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Cause I'm #1, obviously.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.88,0:48:28.89,Default,,0,0,0,,They only brought you here to prop up the machine for me, dumbass!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.89,0:48:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, is that so? Then \NI'd better get going!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.31,0:48:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing, Gun?!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.27,0:48:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh shut up, will ya?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.77,0:48:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,That little shit...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.95,0:49:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Only 40 more seconds under the scorching Sun \Nbefore the race is underway.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.54,0:49:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The light will turn yellow\N ten seconds before start.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.67,0:49:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the signal will change to green and a go sign will be raised.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.43,0:49:13.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The eyes of the \Nworld are on Suzuka.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.39,0:49:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, second by second{TLC, actually not know what's this tokuikkoku}, \Nthe start time is approaching.{刻一刻?}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.78,0:49:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, at last, only ten seconds left! \NThe signal turned yellow!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.91,0:49:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Drivers on their marks! \NWe have 60 vehicles participating today!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.25,0:49:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The light turns green and the\N drivers make a run for their bikes!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.45,0:50:14.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa, an accident just off the start line!\N Down goes bike number 37!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.99,0:50:17.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The lead group heads into \Nthe corner side-by-side.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.87,0:50:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,In the lead, holding onto his \Npole position, #1, Okamoto! {cloth bib displaying a competitor's number; athlete's number​From German “Decken”} {don't really hear what's in the middle, translating lines from manga here}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.75,0:50:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Now they're entering the s-bends! {east course - which is where Suz 'starts' on  - is just a big string of s bends}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.92,0:50:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa! #3 makes a break for it!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.04,0:50:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Bike #3, who had been neck-and-neck with #1, makes an overtake and seizes the lead!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.92,0:50:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Our opening lap is as \Nintense as any sprint race! {no clue what he means by sprint race in bike races, prolly means "driving as if it's a short-distance race at max speed"}{nah, sprint races are much shorter - and typically have more aggressive driving as tyre/fuel conservation/pit strats. don't really appear}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.47,0:50:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,As soon as they leave the cambered corner,\N the top group will approach the uphill section! {"A reverse bank refers to a portion of a road or circuit course where the inside of a curve is higher than the outside." - not sure what to call it in english, tasukete daddy touge }
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.64,0:50:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And the competition for \Nthe top is really heating up! {guess, TLC. By the way, I discovered that this section sounds much clearer on Collectr's LD version, but I still have no clue what's this arasai thing (arrow sign?) that became more fierce and only half-sure about "top" part; }{争い？}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.39,0:50:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Having just passed through the Dunlop gate,\N the top group is disappearing{as there's a short tunnel} into the West course! {I assume you've read https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Suzuka_International_Racing_Course}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.15,0:50:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We're entering lap number seven.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.15,0:50:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,No change to the top with bike #3, Matsui of \Nthe Hamamatsu Racing Team, leading the pack. {would assume it's the name}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.57,0:50:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Onto the second group:
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.11,0:50:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Ooya on bike #2 and Onozuka on bike #5 are really fighting for their position.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.74,0:51:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Maehara on bike #34 seems to \Nhave come off around Degner.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.83,0:51:04.29,Default,,0,0,0,,More info on that to come!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.75,0:51:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So, how's our team doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.46,0:51:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, Hideyoshi is in 17th, with a lap time of 2 minutes 38.16 seconds. {I hope this 16 in the end means fractions of second}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.17,0:51:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What about the princess?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.46,0:51:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Being measured as we speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.26,0:51:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,29th place. Time is 2 minutes 41.25 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.14,0:51:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think they're \Na bit overpace?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.85,0:51:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Gun, how do you manage \Nto remain so calm?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.60,0:51:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Who said I was?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.39,0:51:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm dying to get out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.52,0:51:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,If I don't get on that bike,\N I think I'm gonna explode.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.86,0:51:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't care how fast these other guys are,\N I'm not losing to any of 'em.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.24,0:51:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,No changes to the lead with Matsui on bike #3 leading the pack into lap 12.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.74,0:51:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,He just clocked in\N another smooth lap! {to pile up; to heap up; to stack up; to put on top of another good (condition); going well; fine; smooth}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.91,0:51:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,My watch has a time split of \Nthree seconds for second place.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.12,0:51:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,As you can see, \Nhe's gained a huge lead! {Noun, Suru verb, Intransitive verb\N1. running alone; running solo​\NNoun, Suru verb, Intransitive verb\N2. having a large lead (over the others); being far ahead (of everyone else)}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.04,0:51:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But #2, Ooya, is hot on his heels!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.21,0:51:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And Onozuka isn't far \Nbehind on bike #5!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.12,0:52:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It's too hot... my throat's so dry.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.04,0:52:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd hoped the wind would \Ncool me down a little,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.13,0:52:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,but with the heat reflecting off the asphalt, it's like I'm driving into an inferno.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.21,0:52:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a little better if\N I stay beneath the cowl,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.97,0:52:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's still like I've been thrown into a frying pan where someone's turning up the heat.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.80,0:52:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's hot... so hot...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.97,0:52:46.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, get ready to swap drivers.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.81,0:52:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Ai, can you get the pit \Nsign out for Hideyoshi?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.23,0:52:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.19,0:52:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Haga, get the charger ready. {hope I didn't mishear the name}{probs sound}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.07,0:52:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.77,0:52:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Hagino, the board! {not sure what's it used for yet}{it's used to show where the bike should stop in the pits}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.90,0:52:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,On it right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.11,0:52:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And remember, once we're done \Nwith Hideyoshi, it's the princess' turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.24,0:53:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Gun, are you ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.57,0:53:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I was born ready! \NLeave it to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.08,0:53:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's lap 18 and the leader, Matsui, \Non bike #3 is coming in hot to the pit lane.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.71,0:53:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Their bike will be refueled \Nand their riders swapped.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.46,0:53:16.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And Onozuka, \N#5, isn't far behind!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.80,0:53:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,As a result, the race leader becomes Ooya on bike #2, as he flies past the stands.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.80,0:53:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Followed by Yamada on bike #6.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.51,0:53:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Hamamatsu Racing Team's\N pit work is as fast as ever!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.22,0:53:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And they're back on \Ntrack within five seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.56,0:53:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Ibe, the rider \Nreplacing Matsui, is off!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.56,0:53:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And here comes \NHijiri on bike #16!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.27,0:53:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Gun, keep it together.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.90,0:53:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I know, but I've been \Nwaiting a long time for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.11,0:53:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, Hideyoshi!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.21,0:53:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,That's payback from the start line!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.17,0:53:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That asshole...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.59,0:53:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Gun, what the hell was that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.75,0:53:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.76,0:54:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a great pace. \NHow can you not love it?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.03,0:54:26.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Charging is done!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.87,0:54:27.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Good. Hiro, get going!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.25,0:54:40.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you okay, Miyuki?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.01,0:54:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks, I'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.14,0:54:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The race has been \Ngoing for almost an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.26,0:54:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's maintained its \Nsprint-race-like pace!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.39,0:54:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Bike #3, Ibe from Hamamatsu Racing is\N in the lead and is entering his 23rd lap.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.77,0:54:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But Murakami, #5, from Suzuka Riding is about six seconds behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.19,0:55:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The lineup was just as we predicted.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.24,0:55:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But something's happening \Nin the second group!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.24,0:55:08.37,Default,,0,0,0,,A rider just clocked in a blistering\Ntime of 2 minutes 35 seconds!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.37,0:55:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Ichinose Racing's #16 is really putting the pressure on the other riders!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.46,0:55:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You're so cool, #16!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.34,0:55:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The crowd's more excited to see\N me than that reckless little runt! {TLC, I've just lost my will to live: この必殺カメが出てくっとやっぱ盛り上がるぜ! - this is from manga,}{I'd assume 必殺カメ is a nickname because he's 'slow and steady' like a turtle - whilst also violent? not 100% sure, but works as is}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.51,0:55:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Koma, on bike #16, just did a lap\N faster than Ibe who's leading the race.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.81,0:55:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa there! Bikes #11 and #50 \Ncollide on the entry to the chicane!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.73,0:55:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Will Koma get caught up in it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.52,0:55:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And he avoids them!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.31,0:55:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What's Koma's lap time \Ngoing to be now?!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.32,0:55:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Koma{senshu}'s time just reported to us is... 2 minutes, 34.91 seconds!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.37,0:55:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,He's amazing! He broke \Nthe 34 second barrier!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.62,0:55:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That dude's crazy!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.54,0:55:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Who {\i1}is{\i0} that guy?!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.16,0:55:55.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Check the entry list.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.41,0:55:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It says Koma on #16.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.12,0:56:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That'd be the Ichinose Racing Team: Koma Gun and Hijiri Hideyoshi?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.96,0:56:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,They're both only 17!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.76,0:56:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,They're so young!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.67,0:56:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, they're still \Nin high school?!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.13,0:56:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Now Koma's making a move\N on Yamada in 4th place!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.60,0:56:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,If you give him a target to \Nchase, he's unbelievably fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.31,0:56:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, if there's nobody in sight, you can't light a flame under him.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.94,0:56:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe that's why he can't\N drive like this all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.61,0:56:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Has he always had this level of insight? \NOr has instinct brought him this far?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.20,0:56:39.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether it's on the pass or on the circuit,\N chasing and then blowing past them is his style.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.29,0:56:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And when that happens,\N he's insanely fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.30,0:56:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The guy's a natural sprinter.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.26,0:56:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, Hideyoshi, we're\N changing riders again. Get ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.30,0:56:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.85,0:56:57.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Gun!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.60,0:57:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the deal with \Nyou and Hideyoshi?!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.86,0:57:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not like it's saving us any \Ntime in the pits, you moron.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.07,0:57:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That's just how I say hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.61,0:57:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Same goes for him too, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.03,0:57:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Matsui from the Hamamatsu \NRacing Team is still in first.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.95,0:57:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And Okamoto from Green \NGrass is just behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.49,0:57:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Onozuka on bike #5 is in third, but Hijiri \Non bike #16 is making use of his slipstream.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.29,0:57:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? That one seems interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.25,0:57:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,That #16.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.38,0:57:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,He's my sort of rider.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.05,0:57:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Bike #16?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.43,0:57:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you mean the other rider?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.01,0:57:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,That stupidly fast kamikaze novice?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:33.51,0:57:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I mean the shorter \None who's riding right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.85,0:57:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't you see why?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.94,0:57:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Among the 40,000 spectators here,\N how many do you think know what he's doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.48,0:57:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Five? Maybe two or \Nthree would be generous.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.40,0:57:52.37,Default,,0,0,0,,While they're polar opposites,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.37,0:57:56.83,Default,,0,0,0,,if those two geniuses are a team, \NI think we could see #16 winning today.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.87,0:58:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,That little shit\N thinks he's so smart.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.21,0:58:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,That beanpole's riding it too hard on\N the engine, it can't take much more.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.17,0:58:14.10,Default,,0,0,0,,All I've gotta do is maintain our current position and not put too much strain on the engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.10,0:58:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm able to keep up with the bike in front at only 80% power.{by slipstreaming etc}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.68,0:58:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna preserve as much \Nof the engine's power as I can,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.23,0:58:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,then it's all down to that beanpole and his explosive driving!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.61,0:58:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That's strange. The princess \Nhasn't come around yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.78,0:58:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's no way \Nshe'd miss the pit-in sign.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.58,0:58:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think something \Nhappened to her?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:42.33,0:58:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.96,0:58:45.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's that guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.46,0:58:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What just happened to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.46,0:58:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,O-Ouch...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.26,0:58:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Corner 130R. {https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Suzuka_International_Racing_Course#130R_corner}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.80,0:58:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right, I came off.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.55,0:58:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I've gotta keep riding!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.81,0:59:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,At least your \Nbones are still intact.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.10,0:59:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you keep racing?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.85,0:59:08.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know... it hurts like \Nhell whenever I move it.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.11,0:59:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've lost all strength in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.61,0:59:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.74,0:59:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Courage is needed to race, but a different kind of courage is needed to retire.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.12,0:59:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll respect whatever \Ndecision you make.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.29,0:59:22.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You two just have to work\N it out amongst{that's a word, so shut up spellcheck} yourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.67,0:59:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiro...
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.51,0:59:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do it, Mi.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.01,0:59:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll adjust our time splits to\N keep your driving to a minimum.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.48,0:59:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll give it everything I've got.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.23,0:59:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We're finishing this together.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:52.94,0:59:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Fuckin' dipshit!{leaving this in for WoH}{WoH: Oh cool, I can go full f-bomb :^)}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.15,0:59:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Go die in a ditch!{or lost media yourself idk}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.87,1:00:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,What?! The tires are \Nworn down already?!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.04,1:00:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That beanpole's riding has \Nturned these tires to shit!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.34,1:00:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't be serious?! I bet everything I had on winning here today!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.76,1:00:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,To hell with relying \Non others after this! {unsure about first sentence, usually I'd think he means "I hate to look after the others more than this"}{これ以上単員の世話になるのはいや -  nah is first one imo}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.22,1:01:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,, I'll go pro my own way, \Nand I'll do it for Tomoyo! {unsure about first sentence, usually I'd think he means "I hate to look after the others more than this"}{これ以上単員の世話になるのはいや -  nah is first one imo}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.72,1:01:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But I've gotta win first!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.64,1:01:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,These tires are done for! They're stopping me from going on the throttle out of the corners. {TLC, not sure about any part of this, especially what's 開ける to do here, full sentence from manga: コーナーの立ち上がりで開けるのがどうしてもおくれる}{basically, slidy tires make accel hard, and you've gotta accel out of a corner. ez}{also, I interpreted the akeru as opening up the throttle}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:10.31,1:01:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,All because of his shitty driving! {突っ込み}{Gun charges into corners and wears them down faster, is basically jist of it}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.36,1:01:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.94,1:01:14.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you serious?!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.70,1:01:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It's over...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.99,1:01:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,For both my summer...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.95,1:01:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And my dream...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:25.04,1:01:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the end...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.50,1:01:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.88,1:01:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,He crashed?!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:33.38,1:01:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't gimme that shit!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.63,1:01:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,He's the last person who'd ever \Ndo that! There's no way he would!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.05,1:01:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, but still...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.18,1:01:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Gun, take it easy!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.01,1:01:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, you! {oi kimi}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.10,1:01:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.22,1:01:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't touch me...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.31,1:01:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't touch me!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:48.52,1:01:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Ibe from Hamamatsu Racing Team is\N the race leader going into the 69th{nice} lap.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.52,1:01:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Murakami, #5, is back in second, and Yamada is back in third.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.20,1:02:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:01.82,1:02:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And here comes Hijiri, walking \Nhis bike around the final corner.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:10.62,1:02:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so heavy...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:12.17,1:02:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And here was me thinking racing bikes were\N designed to be light, but it's so damn heavy...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:16.88,1:02:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,That said, why...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:19.01,1:02:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are my legs \Nmovin' on their own?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.93,1:02:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if I bring it back to the pits,\N there ain't a thing they can do about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.14,1:02:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I can tell that much.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.89,1:02:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so far...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:33.35,1:02:37.15,Default,,0,0,0,,How come the pit \Nlane's so damn long...?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.94,1:02:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I can hardly even see straight...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.28,1:02:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Feels like my heart's about \Nto jump outta my chest...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.16,1:02:45.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I know I can quit now, \Nbut like hell I'm gonna...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:46.24,1:02:50.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure that beanpole's \Nwaiting for me...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:50.20,1:02:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And until he gets it,\N there's no way in hell I'm stopping...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:57.13,1:02:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You can do it, Hideyoshi!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.56,1:03:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Hijiri, you're almost there!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.39,1:03:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't give up!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.45,1:03:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all yours...
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.03,1:03:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Beanpole!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:33.54,1:03:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it's mine alright...
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.59,1:03:42.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll never believe it!{lib ish#}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.17,1:03:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Ibe from Hamamatsu Racing has come off on the s-bends and lost his lead!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.59,1:03:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,With this, Murakami on bike\N #5 takes the top position!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.81,1:03:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Ai, when this race is over,\N let's go to the beach.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.15,1:03:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, let's go!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:04.24,1:04:08.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa! Koma's back in the \Nrace after swapping in for Hijiri!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:08.45,1:04:12.33,Default,,0,0,0,,But with all the repairs, \Nhe's a whole lap behind!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.33,1:04:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Ibe of Hamamatsu Racing also managed to drag his bike back to the pits!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:16.62,1:04:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Here come the mechanics! \NWhat will they make of it?!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:21.59,1:04:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't push yourself \Ntoo hard, Princess.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.05,1:04:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Murakami leads into the 72nd lap and we've still got 44 bikes on the track.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.64,1:04:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The lineup of the top group \Nis really getting shaken up!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.97,1:04:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,With injuries like these, I'll try to stay on course for at least 15 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:39.77,1:04:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Matsui on bike #3 is \Ncoming out of the pits.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:42.78,1:04:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But he's more than a \Nlap behind first place.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:45.03,1:04:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And Koma of the Ichinose Racing Team is\N charging down the main straight and after Matsui. {not sure what to make of 駆け下りる here}{it's just like 'charging down'}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:51.12,1:04:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Though, since they've both had accidents,\N they're both lagging behind the battle for first place.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.25,1:04:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's hope they give it \Ntheir all until the very end!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.79,1:05:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Not a chance. No way \Nthey're gaining a whole lap.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.71,1:05:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But that #16 is crazy fast!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:05.26,1:05:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,He's really closing \Nthe gap on #3.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.76,1:05:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Mi!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.97,1:05:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Gun!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.85,1:05:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,For their final rider change, Suzuka Riding is\N replacing Murakami with Onozuka, their ace rider.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:20.27,1:05:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Onozuka on bike #5 is now in the top position, and I don't think he's going anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:24.07,1:05:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, wait! What's this?!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:25.19,1:05:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Matsui on bike #3 is in 7th and has just \Nclocked in a lap time of 2 minutes 33.84!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.78,1:05:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And Koma on bike \N#16 isn't far behind!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.24,1:05:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,His time is 2 minutes...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:34.58,1:05:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and 32.74 seconds! \NHe broke the 32 second barrier!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.41,1:05:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.92,1:05:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Matsui and Koma are\N exiting the final corner!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.88,1:05:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,With 40 minutes to go, \NOnozuka on #5 enters his 83rd lap.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:52.39,1:05:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Matsui and Koma on lap 83 have finally caught up \Nto Hanakawa in 5th place around the s-bends.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:57.89,1:05:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Matsui cuts in on \Nthe cambered corner.{the corner leading into dunlop is uphill --> downhill crest that sticks out, so that's probs what he means by 逆バンク}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:02.56,1:06:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:04.73,1:06:09.07,Default,,0,0,0,,After overtaking Hanakawa on bike #7, Matsui \Nand Koma have once again climbed the rankings.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:09.07,1:06:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,No blocks seem to\N stop their combination!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:16.16,1:06:20.33,Default,,0,0,0,,That's Matsui for you! He cuts \Npast Gouda on bike #21! {would assume 剛田}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:20.96,1:06:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa! Matsui's gone wide\N and Koma takes his chance!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:24.13,1:06:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And #16 overtakes #3!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.63,1:06:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That kid's got drive. \NThings are really starting to heat up.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.55,1:06:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.97,1:06:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Ichikawa, if Gun keeps \Nthe pace of his last lap{\fscx200}—
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.06,1:06:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,He'll make his way\N to the front again.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.31,1:06:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And #3 makes a break for it!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.03,1:06:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it... I'll overtake you \Nas many times as I have to!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:54.95,1:06:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if he is a runt, \Nhe still got the bike back to me.{kinda truncated "with short arms and legs"}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.58,1:07:02.62,Default,,0,0,0,,He was battered, broken,\N and could hardly breathe.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.62,1:07:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And you thought I'd run out of steam here?! No fuckin' way!{swearing now and then is fun, so fuck you}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.13,1:07:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,At last, Yamada in 3rd starts feeling \Nbikes #3 and #16 nip at his heels! {TLC, this "se wo fumiakasu" part just evades my brain}{is it not  脅かす ?}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.26,1:07:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Both are trying to break into the lead with bike 6 between them!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:17.01,1:07:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, they entered their 90th lap! With just \Nunder 13 minutes until the checkered flag is waved! {actually doesn't say flag but I assume}{ye, is fine}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:25.48,1:07:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Bikes #3 and #16 are closing \Nin on Shigeno in second place.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.44,1:07:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,They're closing the gap \Nthrough the Casio triangle!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:30.36,1:07:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the three bikes are exiting the \Nfinal corner! It's anybody's game! {I hope he means this by "it's out of control"}{手がすく w/ potential or passive --> polite negative }{but let's just call this 'liberal'}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:34.61,1:07:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm scared... but \NI'm not sure why...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:42.96,1:07:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,This is amazing!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:44.46,1:07:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody can keep up with \NHamamatsu on the back straight!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:47.17,1:07:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But #65 is still fast!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:52.38,1:07:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Last year, Shigeno on bike #65 \Nhad to retire after a crash.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.34,1:07:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But this year, he's aiming \Nfor the championship!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:57.80,1:08:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The leader, Onozuka,\N is 20 seconds ahead!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:00.51,1:08:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, but here comes Koma!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:01.81,1:08:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,He's giving it his all, \Nbut he can't break out!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:04.81,1:08:05.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not that easy.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.77,1:08:07.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Goddammit! \NNext time, you're mine!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:11.65,1:08:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa, Koma's \Ngoing in too hot!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:13.86,1:08:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.03,1:08:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a crash!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:17.07,1:08:21.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, he regained control! \NNow Koma's driving like a true GP racer! {/riding is same level as; equal to; equivalent to; on par with grand prix}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:22.08,1:08:26.33,Default,,0,0,0,,In five minutes, the checkered flag will \Nfly for this four-hour life-or-death race! {/In five minutes, the checked flag for this four-hour endurance, this life-or-death race, will fly!} {avoided the manatsu bit as was getting too wordy}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:26.33,1:08:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The race enters its final stretch!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.67,1:08:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,There he is!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:36.13,1:08:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,No doubt about it! \NThat's #5 in first place!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.30,1:08:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Bikes #3 and #16 are really \Npiling on the pressure!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:42.68,1:08:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Bike #5 can already feel \Nthem breathing down his neck!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:46.52,1:08:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:47.48,1:08:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Those guys are something else.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:48.98,1:08:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I can hardly believe it...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:50.61,1:08:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I can hardly take my eyes off them...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:52.94,1:08:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe how cool they are...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:55.65,1:08:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all or nothin'! How \Nmuch cooler could they get?!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:58.82,1:09:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The final lap! {imma pretend I can't hear that wasei-eigo shit, kthx}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:00.74,1:09:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Onozuka is making a break for it,\N but Matsui and Koma are close behind!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:20.05,1:09:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I've come too far to\N be overtaken now!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:22.05,1:09:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Their only chance \Nwill be on 130R!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:25.06,1:09:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoever takes \Nthe inside line wins!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:31.81,1:09:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:32.56,1:09:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't get much \Nmore inside than this!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:53.46,1:09:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We're moments away from\N seeing the checkered flag.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:56.42,1:09:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Who'll be in the lead on \Nthe exit of the final corner?!
Dialogue: 0,1:10:01.34,1:10:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Will it be Koma, or Matsui?!
Dialogue: 0,1:10:07.31,1:10:10.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And #16's in the lead!
Dialogue: 0,1:10:10.27,1:10:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The sea! I can see the sea \Njust beyond the first corner! {honestly, no clue why he says daiichi, like the first in what? maybe "the last?"; TLC}{as it's 'beyond the first corner' as the first corner is at the end of the straight}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:15.19,1:10:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,My throat's so dry... it's killing me.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:18.15,1:10:21.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Matsui is attempting a breakout!\N Will he manage?! Will he?!
Dialogue: 0,1:10:21.95,1:10:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Will it be Koma or Matsui?!
Dialogue: 0,1:10:36.04,1:10:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And across the line! {honestly, this doesn't sound like something appropriate for auto racing, but idk what's realy said there and if anything touge would know that better than me right}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:38.59,1:10:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's all she wrote!
Dialogue: 0,1:10:39.97,1:10:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The winners are the\NHijiri-Koma pair on bike #16!
Dialogue: 0,1:10:43.05,1:10:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We did it!
Dialogue: 0,1:10:44.59,1:10:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,He really did it!
Dialogue: 0,1:10:46.05,1:10:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The Ichinose Racing Team!
Dialogue: 0,1:11:08.20,1:11:09.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiro...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:57.63,1:11:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Me, a specialist rider?{note: I assume this is 専属 ? - as he'd be given a specialist racing contract?}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:59.04,1:12:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.09,1:12:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,They're called the \NHagiwara Racing Company.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:02.80,1:12:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The races they arrange make us\N look like amateurs in comparison.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:06.55,1:12:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And those Hagiwara guys saw your performance at\N the four-hour race and want you all to themselves.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:12.31,1:12:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,They want me?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:13.35,1:12:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you say?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:14.14,1:12:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,If you really do want to get into the racing scene, I don't think this is a bad offer.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:20.48,1:12:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Does this mean my\N dream will come true?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:23.40,1:12:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,But on one condition.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:25.95,1:12:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Condition?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:27.03,1:12:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The thing is, you'll need to get \Npromoted to B-class before year's end.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:31.33,1:12:35.41,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you pull out all the\N stops in the remaining races,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:35.41,1:12:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,they can recommend you \Nget promoted to B-class.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:37.83,1:12:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And what's more, \NHideo "Pops" Yoshimura... {https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pops_Yoshimura}{using his full name for clarity}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.55,1:12:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,After all this time... \Nmy dream's finally coming true...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:54.77,1:12:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomoyo! You seen \Nmy Katana keys? {https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Suzuki_Katana}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:57.89,1:13:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't they in \Nthe usual place?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:00.02,1:13:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Why else would I be askin'?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:01.86,1:13:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that's strange,\N I always leave them around here...
Dialogue: 0,1:13:04.94,1:13:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Hideyoshi, can't you \Njust skip this morning?{calling him brother sounds weird in Eng imo}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:06.82,1:13:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, I could...{this is how I *feel* the JP  - let's just assume this is right}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:07.86,1:13:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,They say, if you can't find something before \Ngoing out, it's God's way of telling you something.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:19.75,1:13:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you listening \Nto me, Hideyoshi?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:21.79,1:13:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Dumbass, that's \Njus' a superstition.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:24.21,1:13:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? Found 'em!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:25.42,1:13:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,There they are. Must've \Ndropped them 'round back. {not sure what's this about - pushed to the opposite side}{反対側に落ちた w/ an accent?}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:31.22,1:13:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, I'll see you later.{changed}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:32.64,1:13:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Ain't nothin' to worry about.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:34.51,1:13:35.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Hideyoshi...
Dialogue: 0,1:13:52.37,1:13:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't like the color \Nof that sky one bit...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:23.48,1:14:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The mountain pass \Nsure is great, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:25.90,1:14:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's somethin' else, alright. {not sure how a touge can be "interesting; fascinating; intriguing; enthralling"}{Ahem, I'll have you know...}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:28.53,1:14:30.49,Default,,0,0,0,,That said, this is it for me.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:31.45,1:14:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the last time you'll \Never race me on the pass.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:34.82,1:14:38.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Startin' today, \Nthis highway racer's finished.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:38.12,1:14:39.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm joining the big leagues.{I'm just not gonna shoehorn in the word major}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:39.79,1:14:42.75,Default,,0,0,0,,He looks out of it.\N What's gotten into him?{ just 調子が狂う ?}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:44.00,1:14:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for everything,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:45.88,1:14:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and see you 'round, winding \Nroads of the mountain pass.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:02.35,1:15:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What's with you?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:04.90,1:15:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's called a handshake, Beanpole.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:07.02,1:15:08.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But what for?!
Dialogue: 0,1:15:09.61,1:15:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you worry.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:11.53,1:15:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You're one weird dude.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:24.50,1:15:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:28.13,1:15:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,What's gotten into him today?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:39.31,1:15:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Wanna go? We can \Ntake it nice and easy.{just didn't wanna put "niiiice and easy"}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:41.89,1:15:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, nice and easy.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:58.41,1:16:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You're awfully lively for\N some rich, little upstart! {TLC, only hear "ondore koso me ga gingin ya kono tsukaza}{added in what I hear - last word seems to be from 使わざる者?}{that should do though, right?}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:00.79,1:16:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna beat you \Non the pass this time! { sounds like 俺一遍峠道お前に勝ちたいんだよ to me}{I'm also under the impression Gun still can't overtake him}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:02.95,1:16:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,In your dreams! {guess, TLC, maybe "perfect/great"}{this just せこい  --> せこっ ?}{I do like current line as it is thoug}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:11.21,1:16:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't we just pass those guys?!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:12.51,1:16:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,They're so fast! {can't tell if Perevo is messing with me atm lol} {I'd assume this first in any situation}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:48.79,1:16:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You tryin' ta get \Nyourself killed, dipshit?! {watch me pretend Perevo's note wasn't here in the first place}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:50.75,1:16:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,That got the blood flowing!
Dialogue: 0,1:17:03.89,1:17:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's too narrow! {semai?}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:06.35,1:17:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop, Hideyoshi!
Dialogue: 0,1:17:08.10,1:17:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh{\fscx200}—
Dialogue: 0,1:17:09.35,1:17:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone wiped out! {ye, I hear 転倒 too}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:10.11,1:17:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I can make it! { 噛ませる ?  - as in he goes for the (more dangerous) inside gap}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:38.17,1:17:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,This can't be real...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:46.85,1:17:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You're really somethin', \Nyou know that?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:49.98,1:17:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,A man among men.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:55.78,1:18:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Look who's talkin'. If you weren't \Nmy partner, then we wouldn't...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:04.70,1:18:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,be standing here right now.{lit: be the winners}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:34.44,1:18:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Hideyoshi...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:04.39,1:19:07.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Gun, you gonna enter \Nthe final race at Tsukuba? {when I ctrlf wiki with 最終戦 it's apparently some race which is held in multiple rounds where by winning previous one you're permitted to join the next one}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:09.72,1:19:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll have to for a B-class license.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:12.89,1:19:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I've already missed\N the entry deadline.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:14.90,1:19:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, it's been dealt with.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:19.69,1:19:25.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Hideyoshi said you'd probably \Ncome around, so I signed you up.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:26.32,1:19:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,He said that?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:28.91,1:19:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, Gun, how about you ride \Naround on Hideyoshi's bike from now on?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:33.58,1:19:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It should be an easy fix.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:36.21,1:19:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:38.38,1:19:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I could never do that.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:44.30,1:19:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Gun, what are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:46.47,1:19:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,His blood, sweat, and \Ntears went into this Katana.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:50.01,1:19:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You think I could ride that?!
Dialogue: 0,1:19:53.31,1:19:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Gun, don't do it!
Dialogue: 0,1:19:54.89,1:19:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody's riding it anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:04.45,1:20:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,This was the only thing\N Hideyoshi left behind.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:07.82,1:20:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What will we say\N to Tomoyo now?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:10.33,1:20:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't bear to let \Nsomeone else ride it,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:13.04,1:20:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,but I also couldn't bear to see it gather dust in the corner of some garage...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:16.33,1:20:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's better this way...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:18.79,1:20:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,They can be together now.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:21.63,1:20:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all yours, Hideyoshi...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:24.84,1:20:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Not once did I manage \Nto overtake your Katana...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:30.93,1:20:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But you quit while you\N were ahead, you dumbass...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:35.44,1:20:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,With this, my memories\N of you are gone. {no clue what he means to say by "I don't remember you"}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:39.36,1:20:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll forget you in no time. \NSee you around, Hideyoshi.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:43.65,1:20:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And don't forget to give 'em hell! {ends on a cringe line... smh}
